<i>♪ I'm lonely ♪</i>

24:12.892 --> 24:14.758
<i>♪ It's been so long ♪</i>

24:15.925 --> 24:18.759
<i>♪ Since I felt love to smile ♪</i>

24:18.793 --> 24:21.026
<i>♪ Felt strong ♪</i>

24:21.060 --> 24:23.094
<i>♪ And what can I do ♪</i>

24:24.327 --> 24:27.428
<i>♪ I know I'm not friends</i>
<i>With my reflection ♪</i>

24:27.461 --> 24:31.095
<i>♪ When I don't understand</i>
<i>Affection like you do ♪</i>

24:35.496 --> 24:36.797
-Tess, please.

24:36.830 --> 24:38.797
<i>-♪ I'm begging you ♪</i>

24:38.830 --> 24:41.898
<i>♪ To come and pull me</i>
<i>Out the fire ♪</i>

24:41.931 --> 24:43.265
<i>♪ Come and save me ♪</i>

24:43.298 --> 24:45.765
<i>♪ Like you did</i>
<i>When we were young ♪</i>

24:47.899 --> 24:50.599
<i>♪ Oh please come pick me up ♪</i>

24:50.633 --> 24:53.399
<i>♪ From my lowest</i>
<i>Take me higher ♪</i>

24:53.433 --> 24:54.966
<i>♪ Can you see me ♪</i>

24:55.000 --> 24:57.133
<i>♪ Through the ashes</i>
<i>And the smoke ♪</i>

24:58.934 --> 25:01.168
<i>♪ You say that you'll help me ♪</i>

25:01.201 --> 25:01.935
<i>♪ Tell me I'm worth it ♪</i>

25:01.968 --> 25:03.768
<i>♪ But I don't deserve it ♪</i>

25:03.802 --> 25:05.135
<i>♪ I don't deserve it ♪</i>
- Hardin.

25:05.169 --> 25:07.169
<i>-♪ It's easy for you</i>
<i>'Cause you. ♪</i>

25:12.136 --> 25:13.071
-Hardin?

25:18.971 --> 25:21.038
-Well, that was
one hell of a dream, man.

25:21.172 --> 25:22.105
Ooh.

25:24.872 --> 25:26.306
Are you okay?
- Yeah.

25:26.373 --> 25:27.541
-Oh, fuck.

25:27.640 --> 25:28.840
Your hand looks pretty bad.

25:30.207 --> 25:32.008
Ah, it's not that bad.
I'll be fine.

25:33.041 --> 25:34.741
Bro, you were
fucking wrecked.

25:37.708 --> 25:39.009
-Hey, that American girl?

25:39.142 --> 25:41.109
I thought she was gonna tear
the whole place down, bro.

25:41.242 --> 25:42.276
-She was a bitch.

26:15.049 --> 26:16.049
-Dad?

26:20.284 --> 26:21.117
Dad?

26:23.951 --> 26:24.884
Dad?

26:39.522 --> 26:40.787
Dad?

26:58.758 --> 26:59.591
Oh no, no!
- It's okay. it's okay.

26:59.724 --> 27:01.025
I got you, I got you.

28:13.540 --> 28:15.073
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

28:17.607 --> 28:18.774
Strong enough for you?

28:18.874 --> 28:19.907
Yeah.
It wasn't strong enough.

28:21.375 --> 28:22.576
Hardin, your phone's ringing.

28:22.675 --> 28:24.576
It's Landon.

28:24.608 --> 28:26.242
<i>Mr. Scott's very busy</i>
<i>at the moment.</i>

28:26.275 --> 28:27.609
<i>Can I take him--</i>
-Hey.

28:27.709 --> 28:29.143
Whoa-oh!

28:30.043 --> 28:31.511
-Landon,
if I wanted to talk to you,

28:31.578 --> 28:34.044
I would have picked up the phone
the other 30 times you called.

28:34.077 --> 28:35.977
<i>You know what? I know</i>
<i>you're a selfish prick.</i>

28:36.010 --> 28:37.545
<i>I thought you could help,</i>
<i>but, you know what?</i>

28:37.579 --> 28:39.245
<i>She's-- she's-- she's gonna</i>
<i>get through this without you.</i>

28:39.345 --> 28:41.178
-Get through what?

28:41.278 --> 28:42.145
La--?

28:50.680 --> 28:52.681
Landon? What's wrong?

28:52.714 --> 28:53.914
<i>Just tell me she's okay.</i>

28:55.215 --> 28:56.148
-It's, um.

28:58.849 --> 29:00.849
it's Richard. He's dead.

29:00.882 --> 29:03.016
<i>And, uh, Tessa found him.</i>

29:06.150 --> 29:07.384
-Fuck.

29:07.485 --> 29:09.118
Oh, fuck.

29:10.486 --> 29:12.318
Um. Where-- where is she?

29:12.452 --> 29:13.452
-We're at her mom's.

29:13.618 --> 29:15.152
She hasn't.
she hasn't spoken a word.

29:16.952 --> 29:18.686
-Can you let me talk to her?

29:18.819 --> 29:20.120
-I don't think
that's a good idea.

29:20.186 --> 29:21.086
-Please.

29:21.153 --> 29:23.121
Please just put the phone
to her ear.

29:23.220 --> 29:24.687
-You know, you really shouldn't
be speaking to her.

29:24.787 --> 29:25.887
-Then why the fuck
did you call?

29:25.987 --> 29:26.855
Of course,
I'm who she needs!

29:26.954 --> 29:28.422
You know us!
You know me!

29:28.455 --> 29:29.721
<i>All right, fine.</i>

29:29.821 --> 29:32.088
Just stay calm, okay?
Just give me a second.

29:40.257 --> 29:41.157
Hey, Tessa.

29:42.924 --> 29:43.691
I have Hardin on the phone
for you.

29:43.757 --> 29:45.225
-Um-mm, um-mm, um-umm.

29:45.291 --> 29:46.859
- Okay, okay. You don't have to.
- No, no. No, no.

29:46.891 --> 29:48.725
<i>No. No. No.</i>
<i>- It's fine.</i>

29:48.758 --> 29:50.892
- <i>Please, no! Don't worry. it's fine.</i>
- Tess.

29:52.393 --> 29:53.793
Fuck!

30:09.597 --> 30:10.696
Oh!

30:30.933 --> 30:32.667
-I mean, it's gonna be
me or your mom

30:32.801 --> 30:34.801
and she's gonna make you eat it.

30:35.701 --> 30:37.269
Looks pretty good.

30:38.969 --> 30:40.869
I'm just so tired.

30:43.202 --> 30:43.936
-Hmm.

30:59.373 --> 31:01.939
<i>You're enjoying yourself.</i>

31:02.039 --> 31:05.174
-One little slip
and it could all be over.

31:07.141 --> 31:08.808
-Are you still talking
about my shave?

31:13.443 --> 31:14.709
-I meant the shave,

31:14.809 --> 31:16.810
but if you wanted to
talk about last night.

31:18.410 --> 31:20.643
-I'm sorry, Tess.

31:20.743 --> 31:22.711
I didn't mean to
get that trashed.

31:22.744 --> 31:24.111
It's just with your dad--

31:24.145 --> 31:25.412
<i>I'm not my dad. I'm not him.</i>

31:27.078 --> 31:28.712
Tess, if you don't like it,
tell me.

31:28.812 --> 31:30.712
-I don't like it.
-Then I'll stop.

31:31.845 --> 31:33.013
I won't drink another drop.

31:33.146 --> 31:34.413
-Really?

31:51.351 --> 31:52.217
What-- what are you.?

32:21.689 --> 32:23.156
She doesn't want you
here.

32:23.257 --> 32:24.123
I didn't fly

32:24.224 --> 32:25.689
5,000 fucking miles
to argue with you.

32:25.756 --> 32:27.023
I don't know if she's
awake.

32:27.090 --> 32:28.391
Let me just at least see
if she's-- Hardin!

32:28.491 --> 32:29.525
-Tess.

32:29.625 --> 32:30.625
Hey.
- No. No, no.

32:30.724 --> 32:31.526
No, no, no.
- Hey, hey, hey.

32:31.658 --> 32:32.892
-Do you want him here, Tess?

32:32.992 --> 32:34.425
-You're fucked if you think
I'm going anywhere.

32:34.492 --> 32:35.226
Tess.
-No, get off me!

32:35.293 --> 32:36.593
-Hey, it's okay.

32:36.692 --> 32:37.659
You gotta leave.

32:37.826 --> 32:39.026
You gotta leave
or I'm calling the cops?

32:39.059 --> 32:40.294
-Call the fucking cops.
Call 'em.

32:40.427 --> 32:41.893
I'm not going anywhere!
- That's not funny!

32:41.959 --> 32:43.693
-I'm not laughing!
-She doesn't want you here!

32:43.827 --> 32:45.528
You have no fucking idea
what she wants!

32:45.660 --> 32:46.728
-You weren't here
when she needed you!

32:46.860 --> 32:48.794
Now, you're make--
You're making it worse.

32:50.396 --> 32:51.596
- Tess?

32:51.695 --> 32:53.862
-Ugh,
she's trying to avoid you.

32:53.962 --> 32:54.862
You're the reason she took--

32:59.897 --> 33:01.231
-I'll check the front door.

33:27.403 --> 33:28.836
Hey, hey, Tess.

33:30.337 --> 33:32.937
-It's not about you.

33:33.036 --> 33:34.271
-I know.
I-- I just want to--

33:34.304 --> 33:35.338
I need <i>quiet </i> .

33:36.904 --> 33:37.838
Please.

34:20.181 --> 34:22.414
-I haven't always
treated you fairly.

34:22.547 --> 34:24.447
-You hate me, Carol.

34:24.547 --> 34:25.514
You've always hated me.

34:25.581 --> 34:26.947
And it's fine. I don't care.

34:27.080 --> 34:29.581
But you should know your opinion
means fuck all to me.

34:29.714 --> 34:31.550
And I mean that
in the nicest way.

34:31.616 --> 34:32.947
-You're exactly like him.

34:33.081 --> 34:35.049
That's exactly how Richard
used to talk to my parents.

34:35.117 --> 34:36.350
-I am not him.

34:36.417 --> 34:37.850
-All right. Well.

34:37.916 --> 34:39.949
I only care
about what's best for Tessa.

34:40.083 --> 34:41.318
-So do I.

34:41.418 --> 34:44.485
-The one thing that
I thought that I taught her,

34:44.618 --> 34:47.018
and you may not believe me,

34:47.119 --> 34:51.320
was to not have to depend on
a man the way that I did.

34:51.453 --> 34:53.686
And now, look at her.

34:53.819 --> 34:56.819
She's-- she's reduced to nothing
every time you leave.

34:56.886 --> 34:59.454
-Listen, I'm not--
-No, no. Let me finish.

34:59.521 --> 35:01.820
Yeah, you always come back

35:01.954 --> 35:05.223
the way that Richard
never did for us.

35:05.356 --> 35:06.855
But you never stay.

35:12.956 --> 35:15.292
-I don't know
what you want from me, Carol.

35:15.424 --> 35:16.592
I love her.

35:16.658 --> 35:18.125
I'm never letting her go.

35:18.225 --> 35:20.592
-If you really love her, then
you'll do what's best for her.

35:20.659 --> 35:22.159
And that is up to you now.

35:22.259 --> 35:25.093
Because you are the only person
that she'll listen to.

35:25.160 --> 35:27.860
That girl loves you way too much
for her own good.

35:28.693 --> 35:31.693
But Hardin,
you and I both know

35:31.826 --> 35:34.029
that you can't give her
what she needs.

35:34.161 --> 35:38.229
And that is stopping her
from finding someone who will.

35:57.433 --> 35:59.766
-I can only imagine
how you're feeling right now.

36:03.401 --> 36:06.800
I keep thinking about
the last time I saw him.

36:06.900 --> 36:08.734
He was eating
half my damn pizza.

36:08.801 --> 36:12.102
He was happy.

36:12.169 --> 36:14.336
-Just happy
he had a place to stay.

36:22.371 --> 36:26.339
-I am so sorry
for what happened in London.

36:32.706 --> 36:34.340
I really am.

36:34.407 --> 36:38.575
-I thought we had a love
that was out of a novel.

36:38.641 --> 36:41.042
And no matter how hard
or fast or tough it was,

36:41.108 --> 36:43.275
we'd survive to tell the story.

36:45.109 --> 36:47.109
Hey.

36:47.243 --> 36:51.344
We do. And we can.
We can survive it.

36:55.145 --> 36:57.478
-I don't wanna survive.
I want to live.

37:10.981 --> 37:14.582
I can't keep doing this.

37:14.682 --> 37:17.115
-Tess.

37:17.249 --> 37:20.782
-You don't love me enough
to fight for me.

37:20.915 --> 37:23.250
You gave up every time.

37:30.784 --> 37:33.319
-I tried.

37:33.419 --> 37:35.352
I really fucking tried.

37:40.386 --> 37:42.354
I'm sorry I couldn't fix you.

37:46.588 --> 37:48.355
-Me, too.

37:54.690 --> 37:55.722
Me, too.

38:24.996 --> 38:27.196
-Who's paying for all this?

38:27.263 --> 38:29.363
-You don't have to worry about
money right now, honey.

38:32.631 --> 38:33.863
-Hey.

38:35.231 --> 38:37.898
Hey, hey, hey, it's okay.
It's okay.

38:41.066 --> 38:45.633
Ugh. Hey, I got make up on--
-Oh. And.

38:45.666 --> 38:46.566
And a little bit of snot.

38:46.732 --> 38:47.832
Just a little bit.

38:50.068 --> 38:52.368
- You ready?
- Yeah.

39:35.710 --> 39:38.277
-I hadn't seen my father
for nine years.

39:40.510 --> 39:43.378
But reconnecting with him
was one of the greatest gifts.

39:45.378 --> 39:46.511
Even if it was only briefly.

39:50.379 --> 39:52.913
He had so many demons, but.

39:54.714 --> 39:57.381
he was also so kind.

40:01.048 --> 40:02.449
And he was trying
to be better for me.

40:05.781 --> 40:06.781
I know that.

40:24.853 --> 40:26.386
-You need a ride? Hardin?

40:29.053 --> 40:30.054
-I don't think I should go.

40:30.187 --> 40:32.588
-Why? You were his friend,
kind of.

40:32.721 --> 40:34.288
And you paid for it, so.

40:34.421 --> 40:37.189
-Landon, do me a favor
and keep that between us.

40:37.256 --> 40:38.989
-Sure. Doesn't mean
you shouldn't come.

40:39.122 --> 40:40.589
So, come.

41:14.263 --> 41:16.130
-Sorry,
I didn't know that you were.

41:23.098 --> 41:25.431
I don't know half these people.

41:25.498 --> 41:26.965
It's kind of weird.

41:27.032 --> 41:30.633
when people go to funerals of
someone they don't even know.

41:30.766 --> 41:32.500
-It's just especially him.

41:32.567 --> 41:35.067
I mean,
they're total hypocrites.

41:35.133 --> 41:37.734
No one here even liked him.

41:37.834 --> 41:38.867
-You did.

41:41.334 --> 41:42.402
And even I did.

41:44.869 --> 41:46.769
-I'm really mad at him.

41:46.869 --> 41:50.336
I'm like. I'm like pissed off.

41:50.403 --> 41:53.004
-Hey, you have every right
to be mad at him.

41:53.070 --> 41:55.671
Whether he's dead or not.

41:55.739 --> 42:00.272
I saw how much it meant to you
to have him back in your life.

42:00.338 --> 42:02.639
And I think he is an idiot

42:02.805 --> 42:05.139
for throwing that all the way
just to get high.

42:09.307 --> 42:11.174
But I mean, I'm one to talk,
aren't I?

42:13.341 --> 42:15.275
I'm so sorry
it took something like this

42:15.341 --> 42:18.009
for me to realize
how much you mean to me.

42:18.142 --> 42:22.243
And how much.
I want to be there for you.

42:31.045 --> 42:33.345
-I need to go back inside.

42:42.047 --> 42:43.414
-Okay.

42:54.650 --> 42:55.483
Oh, come on.

43:00.685 --> 43:03.118
Thank you so much
for everything.

43:03.251 --> 43:04.218
-Yeah, of course.

43:05.385 --> 43:06.885
-Hey, could I have a lift?

43:07.019 --> 43:08.386
My Ubers keep canceling.

43:08.519 --> 43:09.919
-I'm supposed
to be meeting Nora

43:10.052 --> 43:12.120
and I'm already late, so.

43:12.220 --> 43:13.453
-Cool.
-Yeah.

43:15.453 --> 43:16.420
We'll see if this one turns up.

43:18.787 --> 43:20.621
Do you want to come with me?

43:20.722 --> 43:22.289
Back to Ken's.

43:22.422 --> 43:25.122
-I should really stay here.

43:25.255 --> 43:26.657
It's been a long day

43:26.789 --> 43:28.691
and I've got a doctor's
appointment in Seattle.

43:28.822 --> 43:30.323
tomorrow.

43:30.456 --> 43:32.291
-Sure.

43:32.357 --> 43:33.524
Vance and Kimberly back?

43:33.591 --> 43:34.759
They get back
in the morning.

43:34.958 --> 43:36.624
They're trying to work
everything out for the baby.

43:42.259 --> 43:45.059
-You know what? I'm--
I'm gonna come with you.

43:45.192 --> 43:46.727
I'm gonna start
looking for places up there.

43:46.826 --> 43:48.193
I'm ready.

43:48.260 --> 43:49.960
-I don't-- I don't think--
-Tess. Tess,

43:50.060 --> 43:51.494
it's my turn
to be there for you.

43:53.194 --> 43:55.862
-I don't want anything
from you anymore.

44:01.796 --> 44:02.796
-I don't believe you.

44:05.130 --> 44:07.331
And I don't think
you believe yourself either.

44:25.267 --> 44:29.235
-I'm so sorry that we weren't
at your father's funeral.

44:29.368 --> 44:30.502
-No, no, it's fine.

44:30.568 --> 44:34.369
Um, ugh. I wouldn't have been
good company anyway.

44:36.436 --> 44:39.203
Uh, I was actually,

44:39.270 --> 44:41.570
I was thinking about
moving to New York.

44:43.138 --> 44:44.271
With Landon.

44:45.972 --> 44:48.640
-New York? That--

44:48.773 --> 44:50.539
Wow!

44:50.640 --> 44:52.140
What's your plan?

44:52.206 --> 44:53.540
Do you know where
you're gonna work, what--?

44:53.674 --> 44:56.206
-Not really.
I. I mean, I know it's far.

44:56.340 --> 44:58.508
I just think
that I need a fresh start.

45:00.474 --> 45:03.709
-Tessa,
it's okay to be sad.

45:03.808 --> 45:05.909
But if you let sadness
control your life,

45:06.043 --> 45:08.176
you'll never have one.

45:08.243 --> 45:12.010
-But what if I just always
feel like this?

45:12.077 --> 45:14.612
-What you've been through
is awful.

45:14.745 --> 45:16.144
But you are so strong,

45:16.277 --> 45:17.878
and I know
you'll get through this.

45:19.445 --> 45:22.179
It just takes time.

45:22.313 --> 45:25.479
And as for Hardin.

45:25.614 --> 45:28.147
girl, just do your best
to pretend you're moving on

45:28.314 --> 45:31.447
and eventually,
you'll believe it.

45:41.784 --> 45:43.916
-Why did you stay
if you knew she wanted him?

45:45.917 --> 45:48.817
-I loved her.

45:48.917 --> 45:50.851
I thought that she would see
that he couldn't give her

45:50.918 --> 45:54.218
the stability that I could.

45:54.285 --> 46:01.987
You know, I imagine if.
if Tessa marries another man,

46:02.120 --> 46:05.120
this is how he's gonna feel,
competing with a memory of you.

46:05.187 --> 46:07.454
-I'm not Vance, okay?
Just because.

46:10.656 --> 46:13.222
I'm not him.

46:19.190 --> 46:21.324
-You are.

46:22.725 --> 46:24.491
Okay.

46:30.959 --> 46:33.593
So, it's-- it's true.

46:33.694 --> 46:35.460
He's your father.

46:36.894 --> 46:40.928
I knew it. I knew it
the first time that I saw you.

46:40.995 --> 46:42.995
You look just like him.

46:43.128 --> 46:44.563
I did everything so wrong.

46:47.395 --> 46:49.463
And I couldn't stand
that you were his.

